Types :
-- int - to store numbers

Primitive and References Types:

primitive - to store simple values
Reference (Non primitive types) - to store complex objects

Type  Bytes  Range
byte  1      -128 to 127
short  2    -32k to 32k
int   4      -2b to 2b   (upto 2 billion)
long   8
float  4
double  8
char    2      A,b,c,d
boolean  1    true / false


